The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Uganda. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Uruguay
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Uruguay. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Currency Reserves by Category for Congo.  Source: IFS Database.  IFS is a standard source of international statistics on all aspects of international and domestic finance. It reports, for most countries of the world, current data needed in the analysis of problems of international payments and of inflation and deflation, i.e., data on exchange rates, international liquidity, international banking, money and banking, interest rates, prices, production, international transactions, government accounts, and national accounts.

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Zimbabwe. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Austria. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Australia
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Australia. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Bangladesh. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Barbados. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Bhutan. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Botswana. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Brazil. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Bulgaria. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Canada
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Canada. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Comoros
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Comoros. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Chile. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Czech Republic
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Czech Republic. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Cyprus. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Germany. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Greece. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Iran (Islamic Republic of). This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Ireland. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Israel. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Jamaica
docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Jamaica. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - New Zealand. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Madagascar. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Nigeria. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Niger. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Peru. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Portugal. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Qatar. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.description: Trade in Rubber and Rubber Products - Saudi Arabia. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

docs.name: National Accounts (Series 20) - Liberia
docs.description: Relations among product, income, savings and net lending aggregates for Liberia. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. The database covers the main aggregates in the national accounts, such as GDP, income, saving, value added by industry, household spending and government expenditure, along with the relationships between these.  The database also includes detailed statistics for institutional sectors (including the rest of the world), comprising the production account, the generation of income account, the allocation of primary income account, the secondary distribution of income account, the use of disposable income account, the capital account and the financial account, if they are compiled by countries.. Different series numbers (column Series) are used to store different time-series versions of national accounts statistics. docs.name: Individual Consumption Spending by Category (Series 20) - Kenya
docs.description: Individual consumption expenditure of households, non-profit institutions serving households, and general government at current prices for Kenya.  Currency: euro. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. The database covers the main aggregates in the national accounts, such as GDP, income, saving, value added by industry, household spending and government expenditure, along with the relationships between these.  The database also includes detailed statistics for institutional sectors (including the rest of the world), comprising the production account, the generation of income account, the allocation of primary income account, the secondary distribution of income account, the use of disposable income account, the capital account and the financial account, if they are compiled by countries.. Different series numbers (column Series) are used to store different time-series versions of national accounts statistics. Series numbers with two digits (10,20) refer to data compiled following the 1968 SNA national accounts methodology, while series numbers with three digits (100, 200, etc) refer to data compiled using the 1993 SNA national accounts methodology, and series numbers with four digits (1000, 1100, etc) refer to data compiled using the 2008 SNA national accounts methodology. In addition to different methodologies, different series numbers are used when data are reported in different currencies, fiscal years, or by different sources. Furthermore, data are stored under a new series number whenever there are significant changes in compilation practices which make the time series no longer comparable.
